description: A chance encounter with a mysterious character named Goodfellow leads Ryang to spring where faeries are bathing. Here, Ryang meets Fanta, a faerie who wants nothing more than to stay with him in the human world. Living with a faerie can be especially trying, but Fanta makes it worse when her rival curses him to a string of 108 doomed relationships!
name: Vol. 1

description: Ryang and Gigi (Ryang's 3rd evil affinity) take center stage. Can Fanta calm the turbulent waters rippling between Ryang and Gigi? It also looks like Fanta has some problems of her own! The suspicious Seho has discovered that Fanta is a faerie possessing mysterious powers. Despite Fanta's best efforts, she is unable to magically erase Seho's memory. Will her secret get out?
name: Vol. 2

description: Samteak tells Fanta of the story behind Ryang's first kiss. Worried, Fanta feels that yet another one of Ryang's relationships is doomed to failure! However, Fanta doesn't have long to contemplate Ryang's romantic tribulations. She must face off with Yuri-a classmate who, for no apparent reason, pushes Fanta from the school's highest flight of stairs! Meanwhile, the scheming Medea wallows in depression. She doesn't seem to have the qualifications to be the Heavenly Queen. To ease her misery, she even attempts dating - with a human! However, Pain, the Royal Faerie Inspector, informs Medea that she will be considered Queen material if she does one little thing: she must help Fanta and Ryang get rid of Ryang's curse of the evil affinities. Medea better work fast, because Ryang has just locked eyes with Sua, one of Gigi's classmates. Is poor Sua fated to become his 4th evil affinity?
name: Vol. 3

description: An argument with Fanta proves to have dire consequences for Ryang after Mungyeong asks him to help save his skating club by competing in an upcoming match. Ryang is reluctant to agree. After all, it's been years since he's picked up a skateboard. However, when he discovers that the opposing team consists of not one, but three, evil affinities, Ryang decides that he'll skate as if his life depends on it ... which, of course, it does. This is one skating match that gives new meaning to the term 'extreme sport.' Not that Fanta's likely to be any help. She's still sore at Ryang over their fight. But if Fanta won't help, who will? It appears that Fanta's brother, Pain, has taken quite a liking to young Ryang. He's more than willing to help, but when this flamboyant faerie does a man a favor, he expects a 'favor' in return. Ryang had better figure something out, because things are about to get a lot worse. A school mishap causes him to simultaneously lock eyes with a large group of young ladies. By now, Ryang and Fanta have become quite adept at vanquishing evil affinities, but how can they hope to survive against nearly two dozen of them?
name: Vol. 4

description: When Bast--a cat demon--steals the "Scroll of Divination," the King of Avalon makes a grand appearance in the human world. However, when Fanta is threatened, the King intervenes...and finds himself in the middle of an evil force that has been resurrected through the power of the scroll!
name: Vol. 5

description: Yuri joins hands with Bast to fulfill each other's needs. Along the way, they cast a mind-control spell over Medea to get closer to Fanta and the rest of the crew. Yuri simply wants Ryang back in her life, but Bast may have other motives...
name: Vol. 6

description: To the shock of many, Bast is alive! Goodfellow just happened to run into Bast during his excursions to "increase his collection." Fanta is preparing for a trip to Sokcho, a beach and mountain resort town, on the invitation by Ms. Yun. There's just one problem: Medea joins them. What else will happen on this vacation to the beach?
name: Vol. 7

description: Locks of Love In order to protect Yeongyeong from Yuri, Fanta may need to cut off her precious long hair in exchange for a Spirit Force's safeguard. Meanwhile, disenchanted from Bast's spell, Medea makes her return and lures Fanta into a trap. Showing mercy, Medea tells Ryang that the only way to save Fanta is a kiss from a person who truly loves Fanta. Will Ryang confess his love?
name: Vol. 8

description: It's a fury of affinities! Yuri and Bast have been plotting against Fanta and her friends for weeks now, and things are about to come to a head. Ryang's amnesia-stricken friend shows her ugly side...by way of an evil affinity. Now, Ryang and Fanta have become quite adept at purifying affinities, but since Yeongyeong's amnesia had also been keeping Ryang's bad luck at bay, our seasick hero is in for a tidal wave of misfortune. Bast has also succeeded in spawning a couple of evil forces, just to make matters worse. One evil affinity, two evil forces, a small fleet of faeries, a couple of cranky humans and a guy who thinks he's a rhyming reindeer...hold on tight, it's going to be a wild ride!
name: Vol. 9

description: In the midst of the fight between the new spirit forces and Fanta's gang, she finds out that her mother, Oreadia, was the one behind the plan to eliminate Fanta. Oreadia states that she chose to get rid of Fanta as the King is up to something himself which put Oreadia in danger. We begin to get hints of what the King's planning--is it to look for a body that will give him eternal youth and immortality?
name: Vol. 10

description: On the last night of Sokcho, Ryang finds out the ugly truth about Fanta. Feeling betrayed, their relationship turns awkward and distant. Hopefully things will get better once Ryang's brother, Kang, comes into the picture. Meanwhile, Yuri kicks up the action when she plots to seduce Kang. What could Yuri be up to?
name: Vol. 11

description: When Fanta and Ryang travel back in time, Fanta gets the rare opportunity to see how her parents met and how their relationship led to her birth--and why her mother has so much resentment toward her children. But in this walk down memory lane, Fanta might not like everything she learns about her parents, as she discovers that some memories are often best left forgotten...
name: Vol. 12

description: The faeries descend to Earth for a pleasant bath. But, not everything is what it seems to be as Seraphina and the other faeries plan to leave Oran, the soon to be named Queen of the Heavens, on Earth. Sindo, Fanta's father, discovers the stranded faerie and takes her in. Their relationship grows as time passes. Sindo begins to express his love to Oran, but villainous Serphina has other plans...
name: Vol. 13

description: Sino and Sindo have exchanged bodies, as well as roles in life. Sindo quietly accepts this fate and shoulders on, trying to forget about Oran and the life he had with her. Sino is obviously enjoying his time with Oran--but Oran is not fooled. Knowing that her husband is no longer the same person, she considers the unthinkable...
name: Vol. 14

description: As Oran prepares to take the children to Avalon, Sindo makes one last ditch effort to keep the family together. But Oran strikes a hard bargain--to accompany them, Sindo must sever his ties to earth. In other words, he must kill his brother, Sino. But before Sindo can make his decision, Fanta's travel back into time comes to an abrupt end, and there is a new burning question within in her...
name: Vol. 15

description: Fanta and Ryang continue on with their plan to resolve the evil affinity within Jinyeong. As soon as Fanta discovers that Jinyeong's old friend, Sangcheol, has feelings for Jinyeong, she comes up with a clever plan to get them together. Situation resolved! Or, is it? It seems that Fanta is too focused on Jinyeong's relationship to see what is happening to her life.
name: Vol. 16

description: Goodfellow tells Ryang that Fanta went back to the heavens. Ryang stands there feeling betrayed. He cannot dwell on Fanta leaving too long because Yusin is heading to an ambush. Ryang is the only one able to stop Yuri's gang from having their way with Yusin. Meanwhile, Heavens Kings are plotting something big against Pain and his crew. Has Fanta jumped out of the frying pan into the fryer?
name: Vol. 17

description: Oreadia leads Fanta to Gwimun prison, where Fanta's father is supposedly being held. But as the two near the prison, Max and his newly formed crew accidentally blow it up! They manage to escape before Max arrests Oreadia, but that doesn't mean others arent on their tail! Will they make it back to the kingdom in time?
name: Vol. 18

description: Fanta escapes from the prohibitory spell and goes into the protective field with Oran and Sindo. Once inside she learns that as a result of absorbing Oreadia's powers, Oreadia has disappeared, never again to return to the cycle of life. Angered by the loss of her mother, and her father's lack of caring, Fanta is lost. But just as the tragic events seem like too much to handle, comfort comes in a surprising revelation...
name: Vol. 19
Fred en Barney Bij de Politie

description: Ryo's and Dee's first investigation together centers around a street punk named Bikky who's up to no good. When Dee and Bikky are kidnapped, it's up to Ryo to come to their rescue and save the day. Afterwards, Dee reveals that his feelings for Ryo run much deeper than friendship, but Ryo isn't exactly receptive to his overtures. In fact, he's not sure what to think or where to turn! Before long, their attention is diverted by a young pickpocket named Carol who needs protection from a group of gangsters who want her dead. As the authoritative officers do everything in their power to protect her, their bond grows stronger and stronger. Soon, it's impossible to ignore the electrified emotions that are brewing between them. Could this be love?!
name: Vol. 1

description: Dee and Ryo go on their first vacation together, but their break from crime-fighting doesn't last long. When the duo encounters a corpse, they're forced to answer questions from local police, and soon discover that four Japanese people have recently been murdered in the same location. With a lot of skill and a little luck, Dee and Ryo will be able to solve this murder mystery before another life is lost. Later, Dee takes Ryo to visit the orphanage he grew up in. When a bomb explodes and seriously injures the nun who raised him, Dee will stop at nothing to find the perpetrator and get even. It's up to Ryo to stop Dee before his lust for revenge leads to murder.
name: Vol. 2

description: Ryo and Dee are on the hunt for a serial killer who murders women who look like prostitutes. They're aided by FBI agent Diana Spacey, a brilliant investigator who is soon caught in the serial killer's web, and it's up to Berkley and the gang to save her. In the second act of the story, Ryo's childhood is explored. It's revealed that Ryo's parents died when he was young and that he was raised by his aunt. It's the Christmas season, and Ryo doesn't want to spend it alone. On Christmas Eve, Dee comes to wish him a 'Merry Christmas' and Ryo is extremely touched by the sentiment. All of their fiery feelings finally lead to one long, hot kiss.
name: Vol. 3

description: In the first act of this volume, Dee and Ryo hunt down a mad bomber who has blown up the 27th precinct. When Bikky discovers the bomber's identity, he's taken hostage and his life is in immediate danger. Dee is soon captured, too, and Dee and Bikky must work together to save themselves - and the world! The second act of Volume 4 revolves around Bikky and Carol's budding relationship. Carol's birthday is coming up, but since Bikky doesn't have money to buy her a present, he starts avoiding her. Carol misreads these signals and is certain he's losing interest in her. Bikky works his hardest to earn the money to buy her a gift...but will it be too little, too late?
name: Vol. 4

description: Ryo is on the biggest case of his life! He and Dee are on the trail of a cold-blooded killer named Leo. They're certain he killed Ryo's parents, but don't have enough evidence to prove it. With a little help from Diana Spacey, FBI agent extraordinare, Ryo soon cracks the case when he witnesses Leo murdering a man...
name: Vol. 5

description: A psychopath is on the loose, killing kids and cutting off their hands. When Ryo's young friend Carol becomes the killer's next target, it's up to Bikky, Dee, and Ryo to take the law into their own hands to save her! As if that weren't enough, Ryo gets an in-depth look at Dee's parentless childhood and the man who inspired Dee to become a cop. But when a little too much information about Dee's de facto dad comes to light, it could destroy Dee's two greatest passions: police work and Ryo!
name: Vol. 6

description: This final volume of "Fake" is so hot, even you'll feel the heat! Diana Spacey returns and gives Ryo some advice about Dee. She warns him that he should just be true to his heart and accept his feelings for Dee, or else he might risk losing him forever. Ryo doesn't know what to do. Meanwhile, Dee and Ryo must serve as bodyguards for Alicia Grant, the daughter of a very powerful Italian mob boss. She's also married to Leo, the man who killed Ryo's parents. Even though she knows Leo is an evil man, Alicia loves him just the same. That night, Ryo and Dee make love for the first time. (At last!) Meanwhile, Berkeley and Diana discover that Alicia has a secret lover - and she soon kills him and leaves his dead body in Leo's apartment. Ryo spies on Alicia and Leo behind a church and witnesses her shooting him because she can never have him to herself. As she attempts to kill herself, Dee arrives and stops her just in time. In the last half of this final volume, Dee and Ryo finally admit their mutual love and devotion...and there's nothing fake about their feelings this time.
name: Vol. 7

description: This book contains reprints of the newspaper strip from 2/29/48 through 5/21/48. It begins the "Mrs. Volts & Sparkle Plenty" story arc.

An angel, who loses his place in Eden, finds a mysterious and dangerous new patron. A poor painter finishes a woman's portrait without a subject and reveals his forgotten past. These stories and more will delight fans of beautiful angels and demon boys!
name: Vol. 1

description: When a mysterious incident causes Mir to lose her magical abilities, she decides to retire and become a student in a normal school--or so she thought! To her surprise, she's enrolled in a school with a special connection to her family. Will Mir's boring new life keep her from her magical past...and her divine future?
name: Vol. 1

description: Mir's escape from Shindansoo Academy may have gone unnoticed, but thanks to Hae-Rang, all witness her return when he leaves her passed out in front of the school gate blanketed by a couple of crumpled ramen boxes. Fuming mad, Mir searches every nook and cranny of campus to take revenge on the scoundrel and finally steps into Ba-Ri's room, where her jaw drops when she sees not Ba-Ri, but a half-naked guy dripping with water...
name: Vol. 2

description: Hae-Rang confesses to Mir that he loves her, but Mir refuses to believe him! An illuminating flashback reveals how Mir and Hae-Rang met as children as well as the shocking circumstances behind the death of Hae-Rang's sister Ba-Ri. Could Ba-Ri's death be linked to Mir's terrible nightmares? The past is only a heartbeat away in this revealing volume of Fantamir!
name: Vol. 3

description:
High school student Hyung-in has never been the same since her friend committed suicide. Fed up with the restrictive classroom environment of her prestigious school and the expectations of her family, she just wants out. But when she meets an orphan and a strange country-boy on the bus, she begins an unexpected journey into the unknown, at a mysterious place called "Fever"...

Chapter Titles

  • Step 1: Number 37, Hyung-In Kim
  • Step 2: Kang-Dae Gets Lost with Bong-Nam
  • Step 3 : Made On Earth Ji-Jun
  • Step 4: Number 37, Hyung-Inm Explodes
  • Step 5: Reunion or First Meeting
name: Vol. 1

description: Troubled teen Hyung-In has just enrolled in Fever, a school as untraditional as its pupils and especially its teacher. Now that shes found a place she just could be happy at, shell have to convince her parents its the right place for her. With a flirty teacher who wears crazy clothes and encourages students to release their frustrations through yelling and drinking, its going to be a challenge. But the one thing she knows for sure, is that the students need a place like Fever, that encourages them to be who they are!
name: Vol. 2

description: Se-Lim Lee knew exactly what she wanted out of life and how to get it...until a month ago. After a horrific car accident, Se-Lim is left without her memory, and all she has is her old diary to help her retrieve the most important aspect of her life--her love interest. Four likely candidates come to her now blank mind--but why do all seem to hate her? Global manga-ka Sang-Eun Lee's hilarious romantic comedy reminds us there's one thing every relationship seems to forget about...
name: Vol. 1

description: Collects issues 13 - 16 of Quantum and Woody. Includes additional material.
name: Quantum and Woody: Magnum Force

description: Collects issues #5 through 8 of the Quantum and Woody series. Includes additional material.
name: KYAG

description: Collects issues #9 through 12 of the Quantum and Woody series. Includes additional material.
name: Holy S-Word -- We're Cancelled?!

volume.name: Quantum and Woody: Holy S-Word -- We're Cancelled?!

description: Collects Ultimate Spider-Man (2000) #28-32. What's it take to ruin Spider-Man's reputation and turn him into Public Enemy #1? Someone dressed up like Spider-Man commiting crimes! And it's up to the real Spidey to take this criminal down.
name: Public Scrutiny

description: After reuniting with his childhood friend Eddie Brock, Peter Parker discovers a terrible secret about their fathers' past a secret that quickly results in a confrontation with Venom, Spider-Man's evil, dark twin. Collects the sold-out ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN #33-39 !
name: Venom

description: An all-new villain explodes on the scene, literally! But how can Spider-Man fight a new mysterious foe named Geldhoff if he can't even find a costume? And will Peter and Mary Jane finally just say what they feel?! Guest-starring the Ultimate X-Men. Collects ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN #40-45
name: Irresponsible

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Ten years in the making, Charles Burns' magnum opus careens towards its inevitably apocalyptic conclusion, with only two issues remaining! This tenth issue is printed with the bleakest and blackest of ink to date. Ripe with the stench of infection, the home that Keith's been sitting all summer is now a safe house for kids with the bug. Meanwhile, his courtship of Chris having turned irrevocably black, Keith's futility is palpable until he bumps into a (seemingly) well Eliza at the supermarket. And what of those tadpoles growing out of Keith's ribs? Black Holemasterfully channels teenage angst and drug-induced paranoia, radiating physical dread to tell the haunting story of a plague that strikes mid-'70s Seattle and only afflicts teenagers. One of our finest titles ever.
name: A Dream Girl

description: The long awaited concluding issue of Charles Burns' decade-long masterpiece of eerie angst. Still on the run Keith remains optimistic about life with Eliza (the girl with the tail) despite the challenges of maintaining his own reality; while Chris longs for home but finds herself travelling towards the dark emptiness that follows each of these plague-ridden teens. Burns' pen and masterful storytelling ability elicits the paranoia that envelopes the lives of these teens living in mid-70s Seattle. This final issue will leave you feeling completely blown away and queasy at the same time.
name: The End

description: Sam Bullit is running for Mayor of New York City on an anti-Spider-Man campaign, and Daily Bugle Editor-in-Chief J. Jonah Jameson is backing him 100%. But whos pulling Bullits strings? None other than the Kingpin of Crime. Plus: Spider-Man meets the sexy and elusive cat burglar called the Black Cat, who claws herself into the young web-slingers life and purrs her way into Peter Parkers. When the Cat gets her paws on a stolen tablet that the Kingpin desperately wants, the crime lord hires the deadly Elektra to retrieve the artifact for him. Collects ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN #47-53.
name: Cats and Kings
Like Making Shoes!!; Mrs. Collins in "Misspent Youth"
Swan Song Part One & Part Two
